§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $A ∈ 𝗦^n$ (i.e., $A ∈ 𝗥^{n × n}$ and symmetric). ⦉

  ‖ $A$ is ❬positive definite❭ if
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ x^⊤ A x > 0 \quad \text{for all nonzero } x ∈ 𝗥^d ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ $A$ is ❬positive semidefinite❭ (or ❬nonnegative definite❭) if
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ x^⊤ A x ≥ 0 \quad \text{for all } x ∈ 𝗥^d ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We denote the set of positive definite $d$ by $d$ matrices
    by $𝗦_{++}^d$. ⦉

  ‖ We denote the set of positive semidefinite $d$ by $d$
    matrices by $𝗦_{+}^d$. ⦉
⦉

